content.location: Walk up to highest section towards the left of the corner and climb up to corner from lower ledge.

content.description: This route lies down and to the right of the “Spacesex” corner. This line follows a discontinuous corner up to a straight in splitter thin hands crack. With sustained quality climbing and a long pitch (for a interior Alaska) this is an area classic. Start with stemming in a sequential corner and one bolt, continue on small gear that gets bigger as you go up.
content.protection: Gear to 1, doubles in the .4-#1 range will be helpful to most, atleast one QuickDraw, shares an anchor with Spacesex to the left
content.location: Look for one bolt at the start in a shallow, featured corner.

content.description: Area directly surrounding the spring. This wall has some great gems and further left there is potential for some harder bolted lines.
